defs.name: Error
defs.value:
pub enum Error<T: Trait> {

    #[doc(hidden)]
    __Ignore(::frame_support::sp_std::marker::PhantomData<(T,)>,
             ::frame_support::Never),

    #[doc = r" Error names should be descriptive."]
    NoneValue,

    #[doc =
      r" Errors should have helpful documentation associated with them."]
    StorageOverflow,
}

defs.name: Call
defs.value:
pub enum Call<T: Trait> {

    #[doc(hidden)]
    #[codec(skip)]
    __PhantomItem(::frame_support::sp_std::marker::PhantomData<(T,)>,
                  ::frame_support::Never),

    #[allow(non_camel_case_types)]
    #[doc =
      r" An example dispatchable that takes a singles value as a parameter, writes the value to"]
    #[doc =
      r" storage and emits an event. This function must be dispatched by a signed extrinsic."]
    do_something(u32),

    #[allow(non_camel_case_types)]
    #[doc = r" An example dispatchable that may throw a custom error."]
    cause_error(),
}
